_comment: Created by EFisher on 25/02/2014 18:24:36 using v2.0
title: How have waiting times after an urgent referral changed?
analysis_commentary: The percentage of people being seen within two weeks has remained largely consistent since Quarter 4 2008/09 to present, with values remaining over 95%. However, there has been a very slight increase since 2008/09. The lowest value of 94% was seen in Quarters 1 and 2 2009/10.
